      "writtenOn": "2026-03-10T16:07:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sorry for the confusion - my earlier comment was not precise.\n\nI was not referring to nested calls to handleCollectionMembers() itself. The case I had in mind is the aggregation flow, where the shared response may already contain Members entries appended by the aggregator merge path.\n\nThis is a needed case when aggregation is enabled, since valid aggregated members may already have been merged into the shared response before the local io_error path runs. Resetting Members here could then drop those previously merged entries.\n\nRef: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/88012/8/redfish-core/include/redfish_aggregator.hpp#1136",
      "parentUuid": "b09946a8_a5295481",
      "revId": "3d6a6e9ed77967c510346f08ec8b8a50edf8c2ec",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
